profile:
We see our customers more than once a year because we provide all year long maintenance service starting from maintaining the windows and eavestroughs during the spring and fall. During the winter months we plow. We strive to establish and build long-term relationships with our customers that‘s why we take pride in ourselves on providing friendly, reliable service all year long.   
 
Here at Richview Windows & Eaves Cleaning Inc. we take pride on providing the best possible window and eavestrough clean. 
 
Our window clean includes washing frames, sills & scraping.
 
Our eavestrough clean includes the following: 
 
1. Clean all levels of eaves including the garage. 
 
2. Snake the downspouts, flush them with water and if the downspouts are really clogged we take the downspouts apart.
 
3. Includes removal of cages, full eavestrough and downspout inspection for any repairs .
 
4. Does not include removal of screens (leaf gourds) 
 
5. We also provide pictures and videos of our eavestrough clean upon customer request.
 
If we see any repairs that need to take place while we clean the eavestrough we notify our customer right away with pictures and videos and hereafter we leave a service recommendation inside the mailbox.
 
Richview alternative services available:
 - Exterior Painting 
 - Exterior Window Caulking
 - Power Washing
 - Eavestrough Installation/Repair
 - Exterior Eavestrough Cleaning  
 - Aluminum Soffit, Fascia & Flashing Installation/Repair    
 - Vinyl Siding Installation/Repair
 - Christmas Light Installation
 - Leaf Gourd Installation
 - Snow Removal

profile:
Bubbling With Pride In Our Work For You!

How does Suds outshine the competition? Well, for one thing, we don’t just wash and wipe!

Our people have an informed understanding of the complexities and challenges posed by the properties of different types of glass fibres. We’re also familiar with the mechanics and designs of windows, old and new - and how and why they are installed. 

Maybe you’ve never considered why those aspects of window cleaning are important. Why would you? Frankly, most other cleaners don’t, either. They just lather, rinse and repeat. 

The team at Suds understands how to go beyond those basics and you’ll see the difference shine through! 

We have amazing reviews because of our transparency - and that’s the crystal clear truth! 

As a matter of fact, our founder - who holds two university Engineering degrees - rolls his sleeves up right along with the team.

He visits clients’ homes and stays on top of new processes, learning up close and personal the different challenges that every type of home presents. That way, we always have the best solution for you. Because washing is about a lot more than just soap and water! 

Experience and talent can be found in every industry. But the Suds strategy for client satisfaction insists on those assets and puts an equal emphasis on high-level customer service skills demonstrated by every member of our team.

With so much to offer, Suds is constantly growing. But we make sure to provide our personal touch at every stop. Our clients recognize and respect that we wash with their pride and expectations in mind. 

And that never washes off!

profile:
C.P. Painting & Home Maintenance was created to bring dependability, neatness, and a smile to the home services and contracting scene here in the G.T.A. After working for several construction companies founder Daniel Powers decided to put his passion for organization and love of hard work to use for his community. We are dedicated to being hospitable to all and respectful to the needs of anyone we can help with our services. 

Forever reliable. The highest quality work. Convenient to you and your family. Our company mission statement is simple; "To provide high quality, tidy and organized services to homeowners across the GTA and to leave every property in a better condition than we found it." With this guiding principle always in our minds when we come to work for our valued customers we strive to complete the best possible work, no matter the service, and to leave a trail of satisfaction and appreciation behind us. Give us a call or email today and let us know what we can do for you! Our doors are always open.

Services we offer: Interior and Exterior Painting, Window Cleaning, Gutter Clearing, as well as seasonal landscaping clean up and handyman work.


Warranty and Terms: For all projects that we complete in the Greater Toronto Area, C.P. Painting & Home Maintenance provides a one year/ twelve-month limited warranty (from the date of contract signing). Our warranty covers peeling and/or blistering due to defective workmanship, damage to property and cracked or damaged windows and will be effective only if the customer pays C.P. Painting & Home Maintenance in full for work completed and retains the original contract. Providing these conditions are met, our painters will perform repairs for the original client on areas where peeling and blistering have occurred, with no labour charge. We will not exceed repairs mentioned on the original contract. C.P. Painting & Home Maintenance’s warranty excludes:

Cracks in plaster and / or drywall
Paint supplied by our customers
Galvanized metal
Bleeding knots
Moisture damage, mildew, rust, rotten wood, disintegrating metals etc.
Interior varnished surfaces
Peeling of previous paint layers
Significant temperature changes
Building settlement or shifting causing cracks or tape tears
Moisture intrusion
Work where C.P. Painting & Home Maintenance did not supply the paint
Damages caused by abuse or accident
Damages or defects caused by fire, flood, acts of god, extreme weather conditions, misuse, alterations, vandalism, negligence or other similar causes beyond the control of C.P. Painting & Home Maintenance 
Matching of paint (the paint can be matched closely, but rarely to perfection)
Please note that C.P. Painting & Home Maintenance’s one-year limited warranty is non-transferable. Should you have any questions pertaining to our warranty, please contact us directly.



Project Rates: Interior Painting-$2/sq ft + $50/door + $1.25/linear foot of trim. Window Cleaning- $5-$10 per window pane (screens and inside of window extra). Gutter Cleaning- $95-225 depending on size and height of home . Seasonal landscaping cleanup work and handyman services start at $50/hr. Combining services (like painting and window cleaning together) results in negotiable discounts!

WE ARE A GLASS ACT
Glass Gleamers is an experienced, window washing company where customer services is as important as quality of work. We offer an extensive selection of professional services to clients in Markham and the surrounding region.

Owner/General Manager, Mathew, brings a wealth of experience and know how in the industry. Glass Gleamers is a safety orientated company with some of the best hiring standards and practices in the industry.

HIGHLY-TRAINED STAFF
Our staff approach each job with the same care and consideration they would if it were their own homes.

QULAITY CLEANING TOOLS
Glass Gleamers utilizes only the best materials and tools, leaving the windows residue free and spotless.

FAST & EFFECTIVE SERVICE
